				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Stats<a name="68725"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 11:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, all valid stuff here.  Here's the way I'd break it down for priorities of worn effects/stats/etc.
<br />

<br />
1.  Instrument (particularly wind/string modifiers)
<br />
2.  Shielding - also spellshield/DoT shield are good, but melee shielding is best(endgame stuff here, but makes a huge difference)
<br />
2.5. Flowing Thought (aka mana regen - FT1 worn doubles our mana regen, so is of the most actual utility to bards, though most clerics won't admit that <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />)
<br />
3.  Charisma
<br />
4.  Magic resistance (roots/snares = death)
<br />
5.  HPs/Mana
<br />
6.  Dex/Sta/Int/Agi/Str in that order
<br />
7.  Other resists
<br />
7.5 High damage ratio weapons. (not super important to us.  Many bards consider weapons with high procs to be of greater DPS utility)
<br />
8.  See invis/waterbreathing/faerune
<br />
9.  Clicky Buff effects (to fill up first 4 slots or so in case you're pulling and don't want to get virtue dispelled, etc.)
<br />
10.  HP regen (I don't see the point in making this a high priority, when we can regen up to about 50/tick with marr)
<br />

<br />

<br />
So, the idea being, to look at any item you might want to buy/bid on from those criteria.  If it matched any 3 of the top 5 or so, it would make a great upgrade probably.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.pravda-of-norrath.com/">Midwinter</a> 
<br > 
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=787165">Tangerine Twist</a> 
