			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Stats<a name="69189"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 7 04 9:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I can't speak for what stats you'll want above 50-some, but below that, I've found AC is king.  Once you have your AC high, then stats are a matter of balance.  A Bard uses every stat except Wisdom, so nothing is wasted.
<br />
I found that Intelligence around 100 makes a lot of things go easier, especially with all of the skills that a Bard must master.  Charisma Definately helps when Mezzing and Charming, I get fewer resists that way, but they last 18 seconds max, so there's no need to really Cram for super high Charisma.  As a fighter-type, you probably already understand the benefits of Strength, as well as Dexterity and Stamina.
<br />
I'd love lots of HPs, but I think it's better to Not Get Hit...  Besides, you can spend a LOT of plats, trying to buy gear to give you HPs as good as a single Temperance spell.  Make friends with some clerics instead, it costs you nothing but goodwill and effort.
<br />
Do get good Instruments and practice all of your skills.  I've found the new Items with instrument abilities quite useful - You can get a decent bonus to effects, without sacrificing Dual Wield.  I find weapons with low Delay to be most useful in the lower levels, although Ratio is still important.
<br />

<br />
Welcome to the ranks of the Songmasters!
<br />
Be Well,
<br />
Clarion</span></td>
